    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-23T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-23T01:30:00-05:00" n="923"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">746E.13/3–2352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ceylon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Satterthwaite</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colombo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-23T12:00:00+05:30"
                            >March 23, 1952—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>530. Death <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> after accident that left him
                        unconscious<note n="1" xml:id="d923fn1">He had fallen from his horse on the
                        afternoon of Mar. 22.</note> has put governing party in difficulties as to
                    succession. Obvious successor wld be either party’s chief surviving elder
                    statesman Home Min <persName>Goonetilleke</persName> or majority leader House
                    Min Trans <persName corresp="#p_KSJL1">Kotelawala</persName>. Former appears
                    polit though not legally disqualified as member Senate. Latter considered have
                    too many enemies. <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss>’s son <gloss
                        target="#t_MinAgri1">MinAgri</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SDS2">Dudley Senanayake</persName> was being groomed for
                    eventual succession and may be selected now despite relative youth to capitalize
                    on patriarchal traditions Ceylonese people and prestige family name. Likely
                        <persName>Goonetilleke</persName> wld prefer <persName corresp="#p_SDS2"
                        >Dudley</persName> as most inclined take his advice. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KSJL1">Kotelawala</persName> reliably reported consider himself
                    as House leader to be obvious successor and feel that failure select him wld
                    constitute intolerable public affront. As his faction includes heavy
                    contributors party funds he probably is in position make difficulties.</p>
                <p>In absence Governor General <persName corresp="#p_SVHR1">Soulbury</persName>,
                    role as officer administrating govt likely continue present Cabinet as stop-gap
                    for few days. Decision can likely be postponed until after funeral <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> Sat 29 which shld give <persName
                        corresp="#p_SVHR1">Soulbury</persName> who due arrive Wed time use his
                    personal prestige (his work as head former <persName corresp="#p_SVHR1"
                        >Soulbury</persName> Commission facilitated Ceylon’s independence) to exert
                    moderating influence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Satterthwaite</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
